# Global Project Rules

## Positive Directives

- Use TypeScript strict mode for all files
- Use the App Router pattern (not Pages Router) for all routes
- Prefer Server Components by default; only add "use client" when interactivity is required
- Use Server Actions (in src/actions/) for all data mutations
- Store all monetary values in cents (integers) to avoid floating-point errors
- Use the `cn()` utility from `@/lib/utils` for conditional class merging
- Keep components small and composable; extract reusable logic into hooks or utilities
- Use named exports for components; default exports only for route pages
- All user-facing text must use sentence case unless it is a brand name or headline (headlines use UPPERCASE)

## Negative Rules

- NEVER use asterisks in any generated documentation, plans, code comments, or UI text - use dashes for lists
- NEVER use the Pages Router (`pages/` directory)
- NEVER import from `@prisma/client` directly in client components - always go through Server Actions or API routes
- NEVER store secrets or API keys in client-accessible code
- NEVER use `any` type - use `unknown` and narrow with type guards
- NEVER use inline styles; use Tailwind classes or the Glassmorphism utility classes from globals.css
- NEVER commit `.env` files

## Verification Steps

- Run `npx tsc --noEmit` to verify type safety before marking a task complete
- Confirm no `"use client"` directive exists in files that do not require browser APIs
- Verify all new routes are accessible and return proper HTTP status codes
